******* Course Objectives ********
In this course, we are going to focus on three learning objectives:

Create essential project management tools like Scope Statements and RACI Charts.
Build a work schedule and timeline in Asana.com.
Compare the different project views in Asana.com.
By the end of this course, you will have a fundamental understanding of project management and will know how to create and use the basic tools of project management.

******* Course Structure *********
This course is divided into 3 parts:

Course Overview: This is the introductory reading material.
Project Management Project Plan: This is the hands on project that we will work on in Rhyme.
Graded Quiz: This is the final assignment that you need to pass in order to finish the course successfully.
Project Structure
The hands on project on Project Management Project Plan is divided into the following tasks:

Task 1: Complete a project scope statement.
Task 2: Develop a stakeholder Responsibility Matrix Assessment. (RACI Chart)
Task 3: Sequence a project task list in Asana.com.
Task 4: Add task deadlines and Owners in Asana.com.

Task 5: Explore different views of your project in Asana.com.
